    "knowledgeAssets": [
        {
            "assetId": "tcel-eaore-control-catalog-2026",
            "docKey": "tcel-eaore-control-catalog",
            "title": "TCEL T9-041-Autonomous-Orchestration-Remediation Control Catalog",
            "assetType": "ReferenceManual",
            "docType": "ControlCatalog",
            "issuer": "TCEL",
            "jurisdiction": "US",
            "effectiveFrom": "2026-01-01T00:00:00Z",
            "summary": "T9-041 EAORE deterministic controls and non-negotiable boundaries. Enforced as an executable rule: AOR-014 (universal cross-tenant / AI-execution boundary). 70 controls (prefix AO- in the source spec) carried here for traceability; the six non-negotiable boundaries are the governing constraints.",
            "contentText": "NON-NEGOTIABLE BOUNDARIES: (1) No autonomous action without an approved policy and action profile. (2) No action beyond delegated authority. (3) No execution using unapproved tools or integrations. (4) No silent override of human decisions. (5) No high-impact irreversible action without the required human approval. (6) Every action, decision, side effect, failure, rollback, and outcome is auditable. ENGINE: policy-decision, human-authority, orchestration, verification and learning engines; 11 playbooks incl. PB-011 Bank-Lien/Account-Freeze Response; kill-switch halts all in-flight/queued actions (Board-authorized restart only); 30 autonomous actions classified by reversibility and materiality; 30 events; 15 schemas (autonomous-action-request/incident, execution-plan/step, policy-decision, approval-request, rollback-plan, kill-switch-state, verification-result, bank-restriction-event, liquidity-impact-assessment, affected-payment-obligation, alternate-funding-source, payment-rerouting-decision, playbook). v1.1.0 adds the bank lien/account-freeze financial-continuity response model. Control prefix in source: AO-001..AO-070 (collides with T9-040 AO-; namespaced AOR- in this ECARMF representation)."
        }
    ]
